{"type":"message","id":"11fc75eb","parentId":"926cd973","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:28:46.687Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我查看更多关于 channels 或 providers 的文档。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_66f144e166324b5ebf1a37fb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"channel\" ~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs --include=\"*.md\" | grep -iE \"telegram|discord|signal|whatsapp|slack|wechat|feishu|matrix\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":15312,"output":97,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15409,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775291325136,"responseId":"chatcmpl-119b4a0a-c009-4bd6-a904-d5b86309887b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2781e7b","parentId":"11fc75eb","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:28:46.720Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_66f144e166324b5ebf1a37fb","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    `channels.telegram.allowFrom` is **the human sender's Telegram user ID** (numeric). It is not the bot username.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    See [/channels/telegram](/channels/telegram#access-control-and-activation).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Yes, via **multi-agent routing**. Bind each sender's WhatsApp **DM** (peer `kind: \"direct\"`, sender E.164 like `+15551234567`) to a different `agentId`, so each person gets their own workspace and session store. Replies still come from the **same WhatsApp account**, and DM access control (`channels.whatsapp.dmPolicy` / `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom`) is global per WhatsApp account. See [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) and [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - **Real channels, not a web sandbox:** WhatsApp/Telegram/Slack/Discord/Signal/iMessage/etc,\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Discord overrides: `channels.discord.threadBindings.enabled`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.idleHours`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.maxAgeHours`.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Auto-bind on spawn: set `channels.discord.threadBindings.spawnSubagentSessions: true`.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [Sub-agents](/tools/subagents), [Discord](/channels/discord), [Configuration Reference](/gateway/configuration-reference), [Slash commands](/tools/slash-commands).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - **Gateway (central):** owns channels (Signal/WhatsApp), routing, and sessions.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    **Simplest:** use a normal chat channel both bots can access (Telegram/Slack/WhatsApp).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw agent --message \"Hello from local bot\" --deliver --channel telegram --reply-to <chat-id>\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:      channels: { whatsapp: { allowFrom: [\"+15555550123\"] } },\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw directory groups list --channel whatsapp\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp), [Directory](/cli/directory), [Logs](/cli/logs).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - You configured `channels.whatsapp.groups` without `\"*\"` and the group isn't allowlisted.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Direct chats collapse to the main session by default. Groups/channels have their own session keys, and Telegram topics / Discord threads are separate sessions. See [Groups](/channels/groups) and [Group messages](/channels/group-messages).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    channel/account/peer. Slack is supported as a channel and can be bound to specific agents.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Slack channel(s) bound to those agents.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent), [Slack](/channels/slack),\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw channels logs --channel telegram\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - `BOT_COMMANDS_TOO_MUCH`: the Telegram menu has too many entries. OpenClaw already trims to the Telegram limit and retries with fewer commands, but some menu entries still need to be dropped. Reduce plugin/skill/custom commands, or disable `channels.telegram.commands.native` if you do not need the menu."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":27,"aggregated":"/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    `channels.telegram.allowFrom` is **the human sender's Telegram user ID** (numeric). It is not the bot username.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    See [/channels/telegram](/channels/telegram#access-control-and-activation).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Yes, via **multi-agent routing**. Bind each sender's WhatsApp **DM** (peer `kind: \"direct\"`, sender E.164 like `+15551234567`) to a different `agentId`, so each person gets their own workspace and session store. Replies still come from the **same WhatsApp account**, and DM access control (`channels.whatsapp.dmPolicy` / `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom`) is global per WhatsApp account. See [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent) and [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - **Real channels, not a web sandbox:** WhatsApp/Telegram/Slack/Discord/Signal/iMessage/etc,\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Discord overrides: `channels.discord.threadBindings.enabled`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.idleHours`, `channels.discord.threadBindings.maxAgeHours`.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Auto-bind on spawn: set `channels.discord.threadBindings.spawnSubagentSessions: true`.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [Sub-agents](/tools/subagents), [Discord](/channels/discord), [Configuration Reference](/gateway/configuration-reference), [Slash commands](/tools/slash-commands).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - **Gateway (central):** owns channels (Signal/WhatsApp), routing, and sessions.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    **Simplest:** use a normal chat channel both bots can access (Telegram/Slack/WhatsApp).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw agent --message \"Hello from local bot\" --deliver --channel telegram --reply-to <chat-id>\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:      channels: { whatsapp: { allowFrom: [\"+15555550123\"] } },\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw directory groups list --channel whatsapp\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp), [Directory](/cli/directory), [Logs](/cli/logs).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - You configured `channels.whatsapp.groups` without `\"*\"` and the group isn't allowlisted.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Direct chats collapse to the main session by default. Groups/channels have their own session keys, and Telegram topics / Discord threads are separate sessions. See [Groups](/channels/groups) and [Group messages](/channels/group-messages).\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    channel/account/peer. Slack is supported as a channel and can be bound to specific agents.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - Slack channel(s) bound to those agents.\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    Docs: [Multi-Agent Routing](/concepts/multi-agent), [Slack](/channels/slack),\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    openclaw channels logs --channel telegram\n/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/help/faq.md:    - `BOT_COMMANDS_TOO_MUCH`: the Telegram menu has too many entries. OpenClaw already trims to the Telegram limit and retries with fewer commands, but some menu entries still need to be dropped. Reduce plugin/skill/custom commands, or disable `channels.telegram.commands.native` if you do not need the menu.","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775291326719}}
